This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a novel end-to-end visual odometry architecture based on deep convolutional recurrent neural networks for feature selection. Additionally, the paper also leverages current Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) for feature representation and Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) for image sequence reasoning, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it focuses on visual odometry, which is a crucial component of robot navigation. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a learning-based approach for visual odometry. 

The paper also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes an intelligent system for visual odometry. 

Finally, the paper also involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it leverages both Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) and Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) for feature representation and image sequence reasoning.
